 ### Proof
 Both triangles $APD$ and $CBD$ are 30-60-90 triangles.
 Thus $DP=\frac{2\sqrt{3}}{3}$ and $DB=2$. Since $\angle BDP=\angle PBD$, it follows that $PB=PD=\frac{2\sqrt{3}}{3}$.
 Hence the perimeter of $\triangle BDP$ is $\frac{2\sqrt{3}}{3}+\frac{2\sqrt{3}}{3}+2={2+\frac{4\sqrt{3}}{3}}$. Converting this to our contrived notation gives $w + x + y + z = \boxed{12}$.
 *)

theorem
